        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:21PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 321 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bluffton, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bluffton, Bellinger Hill Area, Pritchardville, Sun City, Palmetto
Bluff, Myrtle Island, Brighton Beach and Caril Bowers Bridge.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards, TV or your local news
source for the latest information from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
